3:45:33','This is the call for papers for Agile Brazil 2014! In 2014, Brazil\'s biggest conference on agile methods will take place at the wonderful city of Florianopolis, from November 5<sup>th</sup> to 7<sup>th</sup>.\r\n\r\nThe conference organization is working in order to provide yet another high value event to the agile community, with presentations and discussions in various topics and optics. On that matter, we hope that you participate with your stories, ideas and activities!\r\n\r\nThe tracks for this year are:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>General Interest</li>\r\n	<li>Development and Tests</li>\r\n	<li>Management</li>\r\n	<li>Coaching, Teaching and Facilitation</li>\r\n	<li>UX, Product Analysis and Design</li>\r\n	<li>Inovation and Entrepreneurship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nApart from that, we will have a fresh new submission format. Take a look!\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Experience reports (25 minutes)</li>\r\n	<li>Hands-on (80 minutes)</li>\r\n	<li>Traditional talk (50 minutes)</li>\r\n	<li>Duels (15 + 15 + 20 minutes)</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nThis last format is an innovation of this year\'s edition with the purpose of promoting critical thinking and discussions that, who knows, will bring new insights even to the most experienced agilists. It is a single submission with two speakers defending opposite points of view for 15 minutes each, followed by 20 minutes of debate with the attendants.\r\n\r\nFishbowls and Open Spaces will also have their place on the schedule, but they will be proposed in an ad-hoc fashion by the conference attendants, during the conference.\r\n\r\nAs always, we encourage everyone to submit your proposals. Presenting at Agile Brazil is a way to enrich agility\'s state-of-art in Brazil and receive feedback from the community. Plan your submission and participate!\r\n\r\nProgram committee\r\n<strong>Agile Brazil 2014</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Schedule','','inherit','open','open','','280-autosave-v1','','','2014-05-14 23:45:33','